Riddle: “I have keys but open no locks. I have space but no room. You can enter but not go outside. What am I?”
	•	Answer: Keyboard
	•	Clue 1: “You use me to communicate with your computer.”
	•	Clue 2: “I have letters and numbers arranged in rows.”

Riddle: “I’m tall when I’m young, and I’m short when I’m old. What am I?”
	•	Answer: Candle
	•	Clue 1: “I melt as I burn.”
	•	Clue 2: “I provide light but don’t use electricity.”

Riddle: “I have a face and two hands but no arms or legs. What am I?”
	•	Answer: Clock
	•	Clue 1: “I help you keep track of time.”
	•	Clue 2: “I often hang on walls or sit on desks.”

Riddle: “What has a neck but no head?”
	•	Answer: Bottle
	•	Clue 1: “I hold liquids.”
	•	Clue 2: “You often find me in the fridge or on a table.”

Riddle: “What has a thumb and four fingers but is not alive?”
	•	Answer: Glove
	•	Clue 1: “I keep your hands warm or protected.”
	•	Clue 2: “I’m often worn in the winter or for work.”

Hard/Extra Ones
Riddle: “I’m not alive, but I can grow; I don’t have lungs, but I need air; I don’t have a mouth, but water kills me. What am I?”
	•	Answer: Fire
	•	Item: Lighter or matchbox
	•	Clue 1: “I am used for warmth.”
	•	Clue 2: “I am extinguished by water.”

Riddle: “The more you take, the more you leave behind. What am I?”
	•	Answer: Footsteps
	•	Item: Show shoes or feet
	•	Clue 1: “You make me when you walk.”
	•	Clue 2: “I am found on sand or snow.”

Riddle: “I get wetter the more I dry. What am I?”
	•	Answer: Towel
	•	Item: Towel
	•	Clue 1: “You use me after a shower.”
	•	Clue 2: “I am found in the bathroom or kitchen.”
